    {
      "id": "a4280786_0941afaa",
      "file_path": "docker_push_manifest.sh",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "We do the pull so that we can create the manifest for the tag that contains the timestamp. We moved it from pom.xml here so that we can assure all images (amd64, arm64 and manifest list) will be tagged with the same timestamp.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5109,
        "name": "Cristina Pauna",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cristina.pauna@enea.com",
        "username": "cristinapauna"
      },
      "updated": "2019-08-30 18:16:26.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "deab027a_bcbed99c",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "f245159d_2a6bc14e",
      "file_path": "policy-base/alpine/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "Yes, the \"os.arch\" will be available in a local build too, it's available through maven, it's not set by Jenkins.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5109,
        "name": "Cristina Pauna",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cristina.pauna@enea.com",
        "username": "cristinapauna"
      },
      "updated": "2019-08-30 18:16:26.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "45e1a759_6bb3c653",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "697fb0c9_a2898e37",
      "file_path": "policy-base/alpine/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 88,
      "message": "%l is placeholder that is used by docker-maven-plugin to resolve the tag name at runtime; you can check [1] for reference\n\n[1] https://dmp.fabric8.io/#image-name",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5109,
        "name": "Cristina Pauna",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cristina.pauna@enea.com",
        "username": "cristinapauna"
      },
      "updated": "2019-08-30 18:16:26.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "de904813_8de695f5",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "50b14823_99b6377f",
      "file_path": "policy-base/alpine/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 94,
      "message": "The creation of the timestamp tag was moved from pom.xml to the manifest script so that we assure that all 3 images (amd64, arm64, and manifest list) have all the same timestamp associated.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5109,
        "name": "Cristina Pauna",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cristina.pauna@enea.com",
        "username": "cristinapauna"
      },
      "updated": "2019-08-30 18:16:26.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c0aee36f_28cc5e35",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "fbbba536_fffcd052",
      "file_path": "policy-base/alpine/pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 129,
      "message": "Yes, all occurrences of \"cristinapauna\" will be replaced with \"onap\" once we have the final form of the functionality agreed on.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5109,
        "name": "Cristina Pauna",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cristina.pauna@enea.com",
        "username": "cristinapauna"
      },
      "updated": "2019-08-30 18:16:26.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "fa019500_de5baca0",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9ae80b16_7a1f9246",
      "file_path": "docker_push_manifest.sh",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "To give more context: the build jobs are separate from the job that makes the manifest, so the jenkins slave that runs the manifest job doesn't have any images stored locally. What we do here is: for each arch pull the latest image that was just pushed by the previous job, tag it with the timestamp and push it into the repo. \n\nThe manifest is done at the end for all the tags that are already in the repo.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5109,
        "name": "Cristina Pauna",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cristina.pauna@enea.com",
        "username": "cristinapauna"
      },
      "updated": "2019-08-30 18:28:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a4280786_0941afaa",
      "unresolved": false
    },
